<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5415] Batch with timestamp failed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5415</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I create a prepared statement with the following CQL3 using Thrift protocol:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;BEGIN BATCH USING TIMESTAMP &amp;lt;number&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;some INSERT INTO or UPDATE statements ....&amp;gt;
APPLY BATCH
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and execute this statement in a loop, I randomly get the error:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;InvalidRequestException(why:Timestamp must be set either on BATCH or individual statements)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All statements inside the batch have no individual USING TIMESTAMP.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
